2026-05-11 00:33:01,404 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"payload": "{\"message\":{\"id\":\"65581db0-384f-4255-9495-7d49c2bf5cfb\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-10T17:33:01.403161Z\",\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board/astropy-12907/007_action_for_engineer.md\",\"type\":\"ToolCallSummaryMessage\",\"tool_calls\":[{\"id\":\"call_X9eFnJ9ORVj8V7Bw1CP4eSip\",\"arguments\":\"{\\\"path\\\":\\\"data/project_board/astropy-12907/007_action_for_engineer.md\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Action for Engineer (follow-up after CodeReviewer feedback)\\\\n\\\\nContext:\\\\n- CodeReviewer rejected the previous unrelated patch. The fix must be focused on astropy/modeling/separable.py to address nested CompoundModel separability.\\\\n- Engineer previously attempted changes but hit an escalation limit. We need a clear, narrowly-scoped implementation and tests.\\\\n\\\\nRequired changes (minimal surface):\\\\n1) Implement flattening of nested CompoundModel in separability_matrix\\\\n   - File to modify: astropy/modeling/separable.py\\\\n   - Add a helper _flatten_models(model) that returns a flat list of atomic submodels in evaluation order.\\\\n   - Use isinstance(model, CompoundModel) to detect compounds. Import CompoundModel from astropy.modeling.core.\\\\n\\\\nSuggested helper (pseudocode):\\\\n\\\\nfrom astropy.modeling.core import CompoundModel\\\\n\\\\ndef _flatten_models(model):\\\\n    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Return a flat list of atomic (non-CompoundModel) submodels preserving evaluation order.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n    if isinstance(model, CompoundModel):\\\\n        # CompoundModel stores left/right or submodels, ensure correct traversal\\\\n        left = _flatten_models(model.left)\\\\n        right = _flatten_models(model.right)\\\\n        return left + right\\\\n    else:\\\\n        return [model]\\\\n\\\\n2) Update separability_matrix to build the separability from the flattened list\\\\n   - Compute n_inputs and n_outputs per atomic submodel\\\\n   - Build cumulative offsets for input/output indices\\\\n   - For each pair of atomic submodels i,j, determine if any output of i depends on any input of j (or use existing logic but mapped to atomic indices)\\\\n   - Ensure block construction uses the atomic mapping so nested compounds do not generate repeated True blocks\\\\n\\\\n3) Add unit tests\\\\n   - Modify astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py to add tests for nested compound models, e.g.:\\\\n       cm = m.Linear1D(10) & m.Linear1D(5)\\\\n       top = m.Pix2Sky_TAN() & cm\\\\n       assert separability_matrix(top) == expected_matrix\\\\n   - Include variations: top-level nesting, deeper nesting, and ensure the two Linear1D blocks are separable from each other.\\\\n\\\\n4) Keep changes localized; do NOT modify unrelated files (convolution, units, etc.) in this PR.\\\\n\\\\n5) Run tests:\\\\n   - pytest astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6]\\\\n   - pytest astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]\\\\n   - Then run the full modeling separable test module.\\\\n\\\\nIf you encounter pytest collection failures (SyntaxError/ImportError), do not edit tests \u2014 tests are auto-applied by the harness. Run `pytest --collect-only` to diagnose.\\\\n\\\\nDeliverables:\\\\n- A focused patch touching only separable.py and tests\\\\n- Local test run results (or commit with tests passing)\\\\n\\\\nIf you want, prepare the actual patch content here and we'll route it for review.\\\\n\\\\nAssignee: Engineer\\\\nPriority: high\\\\nEstimate: 2-4h\\\\n\\\"}\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\"}],\"results\":[{\"content\":\"Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board/astropy-12907/007_action_for_engineer.md\",\"name\":\"board_write_file\",\"call_id\":\"call_X9eFnJ9ORVj8V7Bw1CP4eSip\",\"is_error\":false}]}}", "sender": "ProjectManager_9c816608-a04b-4baf-b024-b748bf4b2c3a/9c816608-a04b-4baf-b024-b748bf4b2c3a", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
