2026-05-11 00:33:17,669 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"type": "ToolCall", "tool_name": "board_write_file", "arguments": {"path": "data/project_board/astropy-12907/008_pm_summary_and_next_steps.md", "content": "PM Summary and Next Steps\n\nCurrent status\n- Issue: separability_matrix computes incorrect matrix for nested CompoundModels.\n- Failing tests: astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py::test_separable[compound_model6-result6] and ::test_separable[compound_model9-result9]\n- Tickets created: 000_diagnosis, 001_fix, 002_tests, 003_review, 004_qa\n- Engineer attempted a patch but modified unrelated files (convolution and units) and CodeReviewer rejected that patch as it did not address separability_matrix.\n- Engineer hit an escalation hard-stop and requested the task be marked failed or for the PM to declare best available state.\n\nWhat must be done (minimal and focused)\n1) Revert any unrelated changes previously committed for this issue (convolution, utils, quantity_helper). The fix must be local to astropy/modeling/separable.py and the modeling tests.\n2) Implement a minimal fix in astropy/modeling/separable.py: flatten nested CompoundModel instances before computing the separability matrix, so input/output index mapping is computed from atomic submodels in evaluation order.\n   - Add helper _flatten_models(model) that returns a flat list of atomic submodels preserving evaluation order. Use CompoundModel detection from astropy.modeling.core.\n   - Use flattened list to compute n_inputs/n_outputs per atomic submodel, compute cumulative offsets, and build the separability matrix from these atomic blocks.\n   - Keep change minimal and well-commented.\n3) Add tests to astropy/modeling/tests/test_separable.py covering nested CompoundModel cases (examples from issue). Tests should assert expected boolean matrix blocks for nested combos.\n4) Run pytest --collect-only first (if necessary) to ensure no SyntaxError/ImportError, then run the two failing tests, then run the full separable tests.\n\nConcrete pseudocode to implement (to be used in separable.py)\n\nfrom astropy.modeling.core import CompoundModel\n\ndef _flatten_models(model):\n    \"\"\"Return a flat list of atomic (non-CompoundModel) submodels preserving evaluation order.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(model, CompoundModel):\n        # CompoundModel may expose left/right or submodels; ensure correct traversal order\n        left = _flatten_models(model.left)\n        right = _flatten_models(model.right)\n        return left + right\n    else:\n        return [model]\n\n# In separability_matrix:\nsubmodels = _flatten_models(model)\nin_counts = [m.n_inputs for m in submodels]\nout_counts = [m.n_outputs for m in submodels]\n# compute offsets\nin_offsets = np.cumsum([0] + in_counts[:-1])\nout_offsets = np.cumsum([0] + out_counts[:-1])\n# build full boolean matrix of shape (sum(out_counts), sum(in_counts)) using atomic-block logic\n\nNotes and constraints\n- Do not edit test files (tests are auto-applied by the harness). If tests fail to collect, run pytest --collect-only to diagnose.\n- Keep the patch minimal: only change separable.py and add tests.\n- After implementation, route to CodeReviewer for review and then to QA.\n\nAssignment\n- Next assignee: Engineer (a senior engineer if possible, because the previous engineer hit an escalation stop). Please pick up tickets 000_diagnosis and 001_fix first.\n\nDeliverables\n- Focused commit(s) modifying astropy/modeling/separable.py and adding tests. Revert unrelated changes if any were committed in the branch.\n- Local test run showing the two failing tests now pass (or CI output)\n\nIf the Engineer agrees, I will transfer the issue to them now to implement the fix and add tests. After they push the patch, route to CodeReviewer for review.\n"}, "result": "Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/example-study/mas_centralize/astropy__astropy-12907/repeat_1/project_board/astropy-12907/008_pm_summary_and_next_s